      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="change-color-status" data-step-uuid="9135ab1a-83dc-4e42-92f7-186dc9ad4400">
    <h2 id="change-color-status" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Change Color Status</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/007/725/414/original/472c73f2-91a2-48ac-b5ad-2ca5e776b65a.png" srcset="" alt="Change Color Status" height="398" width="774">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_652f1f89-7455-4736-a46e-c89b2a302b84" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Select the new color for the status. The check mark indicates the selected color [1], and the hex color code displays in the text field [2]. </p>
<p>If you want to use a color not shown in the window, you can enter the color's hex code directly in in the text field. The hex field will display a warning icon if the hex code is not valid. </p>
<p>Click the <strong>Apply</strong> button [3].</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

